00191 void Calvin::loadHeader(affymetrix_calvin_io::GenericDataHeader& Header, CalvinHeader& header)
00192 {
00193         AffxString strValue;
00194         header.reserve(Header.GetNameValParamCnt() + 4);
00195         //File header
00196         header.add(new CalvinParameter("FileIdentifier", CalvinValue::AsciiType, Header.GetFileId()));
00197         header.add(new CalvinParameter("FileTypeIdentifier", CalvinValue::AsciiType, Header.GetFileTypeId()));
00198         header.add(new CalvinParameter("FileLocale", CalvinValue::TextType, StringUtils::ConvertWCSToMBS(Header.GetLocale())));
00199 
00200         // Header Parameters
00201         int iParamCount = Header.GetNameValParamCnt();
00202         affymetrix_calvin_parameter::ParameterNameValueType param;
00203         for (int iParamIndex = 0; (iParamIndex < iParamCount); iParamIndex++)
00204         {
00205                 param = Header.GetNameValParam(iParamIndex);
00206                 strValue.clear();
00207                 switch (param.GetParameterType())
00208                 {
00209                 case CalvinValue::Int8Type:
00210                         strValue = ::getInt(param.GetValueInt8());
00211                         break;
00212                 case CalvinValue::UInt8Type:
00213                         strValue = ::getInt(param.GetValueUInt8());
00214                         break;
00215                 case CalvinValue::Int16Type:
00216                         strValue = ::getInt(param.GetValueInt16());
00217                         break;
00218                 case CalvinValue::UInt16Type:
00219                         strValue = ::getInt(param.GetValueUInt16());
00220                         break;
00221                 case CalvinValue::Int32Type:
00222                         strValue = ::getInt(param.GetValueInt32());
00223                         break;
00224                 case CalvinValue::UInt32Type:
00225                         strValue = ::getUnsignedInt(param.GetValueUInt32());
00226                         break;
00227                 case CalvinValue::FloatType:
00228                         strValue = ::getDouble(param.GetValueFloat(), 10);
00229                         break;
00230                 case CalvinValue::AsciiType:
00231                         strValue = param.GetValueAscii();
00232                         break;
00233                 case CalvinValue::TextType:
00234                         strValue = StringUtils::ConvertWCSToMBS(param.GetValueText());
00235                         break;
00236                 default:
00237                         break;
00238                 }
00239                 header.add(new CalvinParameter(StringUtils::ConvertWCSToMBS(param.GetName()), (CalvinValue::ParameterType)param.GetParameterType(), strValue));
00240         }
00241 }

00271                                 {
00272                                         for (int iColIndex = 0; (iColIndex < pSet->getCalvinValues().getAt(iRowIndex)->getCount()); iColIndex++)

00274                                                 CalvinValue* p = pSet->getCalvinValues().getAt(iRowIndex)->getAt(iColIndex);
00275                                                 if (iColIndex != 0) {file.write("\t");}
00276                                                 if (p->getParameterType() == CalvinValue::FloatType)
00277                                                 {
00278                                                         file.write(::getDouble(::getDouble(p->getValue()), iPrecision).c_str());
00279                                                 }
00280                                                 else
00281                                                 {
00282                                                         file.write(p->getValue().c_str());
00283                                                 }

00310 {
00311         if (bCheckHeader)
00312         {
00313                 if (!equivalentHeader("File ", getCalvinHeader(), that.getCalvinHeader(), setIgnore, mapEpsilon, fEpsilon, fFraction)) {return false;}

00320                 {
00321                         if (!equivalentHeader("Parent " + ::getInt(iParentIndex + 1) + " ", *this->getParentCalvinHeaders().getAt(iParentIndex), *that.getParentCalvinHeaders().getAt(iParentIndex), setIgnore, mapEpsilon, fEpsilon, fFraction)) {return false;}
00322                 }
00323         }
00324         if (this->getCalvinDataGroups().getCount() != that.getCalvinDataGroups().getCount())
00325         {
00326                 Verbose::out(1, "Files do not have the same number of Data Groups.");
00327                 return false;

00330         {
00331                 CalvinDataGroup* pThisGroup = this->getCalvinDataGroups().getAt(iGroupIndex);

00333                 if (pThisGroup->getName() != pThatGroup->getName())
00334                 {
00335                         Verbose::out(1, "File Data Group name mismatch: " + pThisGroup->getName() + " != " + pThatGroup->getName());

00347                         if (pThisSet->getName() != pThatSet->getName())
00348                         {

00360                                 return false;

00409 bool Calvin::equivalentHeader(const AffxString& strPrompt, CalvinHeader& headerThis, CalvinHeader& headerThat, std::set<std::string>& setIgnore, std::map<std::string, float>& mapEpsilon, float fEpsilon, float fFraction)
00410 {
00411         if (headerThis.getCount() != headerThat.getCount())
00412         {
00413                 Verbose::out(1, "WARNING: " + strPrompt + "Header does not have the same number of Parameters.");
00414 //              return false;
00415         }
00416         // Note that this check allows the 'that' header to have more items in it than the 'this' header.
00417         // Assuming that the 'this' header is the gold data and the 'that' header is the test data.
00418         headerThat.quickSort(0); // By Parameter Name
00419         for (int iIndex = 0; (iIndex < headerThis.getCount()); iIndex++)
00420         {
00421                 CalvinParameter* pThis = headerThis.getAt(iIndex);
00422                 int iSearchIndex = headerThat.binarySearch(*pThis, 0); // By Parameter Name
00423                 if (iSearchIndex != -1)
00424                 {
00425                         CalvinParameter* pThat = headerThat.getAt(iSearchIndex);
00426                         if (!equivalentParameter(strPrompt, *pThis, *pThat, setIgnore, mapEpsilon, fEpsilon, fFraction)) {return false;}
00427                 }
00428                 else
00429                 {
00430                         Verbose::out(1, strPrompt + "Header parameter " + pThis->getName() + " is missing.");
00431                         return false;
00432                 }
00433         }
00434         return true;
00435 }

00437 bool Calvin::equivalentParameter(const AffxString& strPrompt, CalvinParameter& This, CalvinParameter& That, std::set<std::string>& setIgnore, std::map<std::string, float>& mapEpsilon, float fEpsilon, float fFraction)
00438 {
00439         if (This.getName() != That.getName())
00440         {
00441                 Verbose::out(1, strPrompt + "Header Parameter name mismatch: " + This.getName() + " != " + That.getName());
00442                 return false;
00443         }
00444         if (This.getParameterType() != That.getParameterType())
00445         {
00446                 Verbose::out(1, strPrompt + "Header Parameter Type mismatch for parameter: " + This.getName());
00447                 return false;
00448         }               
00449         if (setIgnore.find(This.getName()) == setIgnore.end()) 
00450         {
00451                 float fEps = fEpsilon;
00452                 if (mapEpsilon.find(This.getName()) != mapEpsilon.end()) {fEps = mapEpsilon.find(This.getName())->second;}
00453                 if (This.getParameterType() == CalvinValue::FloatType)
00454                 {
00455                         float fThis = (float)::getDouble(This.getValue());
00456                         float fThat = (float)::getDouble(That.getValue());
00457                         float fEpsilon2 = fFraction*max( fabs(fThis), fabs(fThat) );
00458                         if (fabs(fThis - fThat) > max(fEps,fEpsilon2))
00459                         {
00460                                 Verbose::out(1, strPrompt + "Header Parameter Value is out of spec. for " + This.getName() + "\tDifference = " + ::getDouble(fabs(fThis - fThat), 10) + "\tEpsilon = " + ::getDouble(fEps, 10));
00461                                 return false;
00462                         }
00463                 }
00464                 else if (This.getValue() != That.getValue())
00465                 {
00466                         Verbose::out(1, strPrompt + "Header Parameter Value mismatch for " + This.getName() + "\t" + This.getValue() + " != " + That.getValue());
00467                         return false;
00468                 }
00469         }
00470         return true;
00471 }
